    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "). 2 HCQ is widely used to treat dermatologic and rheumatologic diseases and it has been described as one of the main drugs triggering acute generalized exanthematous pustulosis (AGEP). 3, 4 Only one single case of AGEP induced by HIV post-exposure prophylaxis with Lopinavir/Ritonavir has been reported. 5 A 70-year-old Italian woman with no personal/family history of psoriasis was admitted to our clinic for the rapid onset of a diffuse, pruritic pustular eruption. Three weeks before she had been treated for SARS-CoV-2 pneumonia with Lopinavir/Ritonavir 200/50mg 2 tables and HCQ 200 mg bid for 10 days with a good response. Three days after the withdrawal of the treatment she referred the onset of a skin eruption on the upper arms, rapidly spreading to the trunk. She consulted her primary care physician and began treatment with oral prednisone 0.3 mg/Kg daily.",
